games.summary: CHARLOTTE, N.C. Collin Sexton led the Hornets with 22 points.
blurbs: ⬆️ Collin Murray-Boyles (TOR) played 32 min (season avg: 19). 4 pts, 15 reb, 3 ast.

games.summary: Isaiah Stewart scored a career-high 31 points to help the short-handed Detroit Pistons beat the Chicago Bulls 108-93 on Wednesday night. Chicago led 77-76 at the end of the third quarter, but Detroit scored the first seven points of the fourth to go up 83-77.
blurbs: 📋 Paul Reed (DET) made just his 5th start this season. 9 pts, 6 reb.
🆕 Jaden Ivey (DET) made his first start of the season. 20 min, 8 pts.
⬆️ Daniss Jenkins (DET) played 28 min (season avg: 16). 2 pts, 6 reb, 15 ast.

games.summary: Joel Embiid scored 28 points, Paul George added 23 and all of Philadelphia's starters scored in double-figures as the 76ers beat the Washington Wizards 131-110 on Wednesday night. returned to the Philadelphia lineup from a left knee injury and scored two points in his first game since Nov.
blurbs: ⬆️ Anthony Gill (WSH) played 20 min (season avg: 4). 8 pts, 4 reb, 0 ast.
⬆️ Malaki Branham (WSH) played 31 min (season avg: 9). 8 pts, 4 reb, 8 ast.
⬆️ AJ Johnson (WSH) played 20 min (season avg: 6). 6 pts, 4 reb, 2 ast.

games.summary: Jamal Murray had 22 points and 17 assists and Peyton Watson scored 30 for the Denver Nuggets , who went on a 14-0 run to rally from a fourth-quarter deficit and pull away to beat the Boston Celtics 114-110 on Wednesday night. Boston trailed 107-95 and cut it to three points in the final seconds, but it was too late.
blurbs: 📋 DaRon Holmes II (DEN) made just his 4th start this season. 6 pts, 2 reb.
⬆️ Zeke Nnaji (DEN) played 25 min (season avg: 10). 12 pts, 2 reb, 1 ast.

games.summary: Zaccharie Risacher scored 25 points, Jalen Johnson added 19 and seven Atlanta players scored in double figures Wednesday night in a 117-100 win over the New Orleans Pelicans as the Hawks traded four-time All-Star Trae Young to Washington .
blurbs: 📋 Mouhamed Gueye (ATL) made just his 4th start this season. 10 pts, 11 reb.
📋 Karlo Matkovic (NO) made just his 2nd start this season. 2 pts, 4 reb.
⬆️ Micah Peavy (NO) played 29 min (season avg: 15). 11 pts, 5 reb, 6 ast.
⬆️ Bryce McGowens (NO) played 37 min (season avg: 19). 20 pts, 2 reb, 3 ast.

games.summary: Paolo Banchero banked in a 3-pointer from the top of the key at the overtime buzzer to give the Orlando Magic a 104-103 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Wednesday night. Banchero scored 30 points to lead Orlando.
blurbs: 📋 Ziaire Williams (BKN) made just his 4th start this season. 5 pts, 2 reb.
📋 Day'Ron Sharpe (BKN) made just his 3rd start this season. 5 pts, 7 reb.
⬆️ Noah Penda (ORL) played 31 min (season avg: 12). 13 pts, 11 reb, 1 ast.

games.summary: Karl-Anthony Towns had 20 points, 11 rebounds and a season-high seven assists, Jalen Brunson scored 26 points and the New York Knicks snapped their four-game losing streak with a 123-111 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
MEMPHIS, Tenn. -- — Dillon Brooks scored 21 points, fellow former Memphis player Grayson Allen added 19 and the Phoenix Suns routed the Grizzlies 117-98 on Wednesday night.
blurbs: 📋 GG Jackson (MEM) made just his 3rd start this season. 11 pts, 5 reb.
⬆️ Olivier-Maxence Prosper (MEM) played 26 min (season avg: 11). 8 pts, 7 reb, 0 ast.

games.summary: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 46 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Utah Jazz 129-125 in overtime Wednesday night to snap a two-game losing skid. Gilgeous-Alexander calmly made a shot from near the free-throw line at the regulation buzzer to force overtime, then scored nine points in the extra period.
blurbs: ⬆️ Brice Sensabaugh (UTAH) played 32 min (season avg: 20). 13 pts, 5 reb, 1 ast.
⬆️ Walter Clayton Jr. (UTAH) played 27 min (season avg: 17). 15 pts, 6 reb, 4 ast.

games.summary: Keldon Johnson had 27 points, Victor Wembanyama added 16 points and 14 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs overcame 38 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists from Luka Doncic to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 107-91 on Wednesday night. He had 30 points in 20 minutes in a 106-105 loss at Memphis and followed that up with his 15th double-double this season.
blurbs: 📋 Jarred Vanderbilt (LAL) made just his 3rd start this season. 4 pts, 0 reb.

games.summary: Stephen Curry had 31 points, highlighted by a step-back 3-pointer with 26 seconds left, and added seven assists and seven rebounds to help the Golden State Warriors beat the Milwaukee Bucks 120-113 on Wednesday night. He made his first from deep at the 4:44 mark of the opening quarter and scored 14 points by halftime.
PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Deni Avdija had a season-high 41 points and the Portland Trail Blazers won their fourth straight with a wild 103-102 victory over the Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
